# Tailwind CSS

## Rules
- Prefer utilities over custom CSS. Use `@apply` sparingly in extracted component classes when repetition is high.
- Keep class lists readable. If a class list becomes unwieldy, extract a small presentational component or use variant groups where supported.
- Ensure accessible focus states with `focus-visible:` and adequate color contrast. Do not remove outlines without providing an accessible replacement.
- Use responsive and state variants (`sm: md: lg: hover: disabled:`) consistently; design mobile-first.
- Centralize theme tokens (colors, spacing, radii) in `tailwind.config.*`. Avoid ad-hoc hex values in templates; prefer named theme colors.
- Avoid global CSS resets beyond Tailwind's base; keep global styles minimal.

## Example
```html
<button
  class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-slate-900 px-4 py-2 text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-slate-800 focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-2"
  type="button"
>
  Start vibing!
</button>
```

